parameters: \pop[2]This is the first time we've all assembled at Taylor's place.
\pop[2]But I know we've all been here at least once or twice on our own.
\pop[2]I'm glad that these new developments didn't cause group panic.
\pop[2]If anything, it was more like group caution; which was what we needed.
\pop[2]Paranoia would do nothing but cloud our judgment, and lead to our failure.
\pop[2]I have no idea what to do in the meantime, and everybody seems a little bit bored.
\pop[3]Well, The Quantum Leap is in three days.
And the anime convention is a few days later.
I guess we can still have some fun while we lay low.
\pop[4]And both events will have large crowds.
It'll be easy to blend in when we leave our houses.
\pop[3]But what do we do until then?
I have a \c[14]lot\c[0] to watch before the con.
\pop[3]I wouldn't mind seeing what \c[14]that's\c[0] all about.
It's kind of like our R&R campaign, but animated, right?
\pop[3]As the GM, I'm inclined to agree.
\pop[3]No better form of escapism than role-playing.
\pop[3]I like the sound of all these things.
Who says the isolation has to be dull, right?
\pop[4]Right. Well, I'm still a bit of an outlier here.
Delta, too. We both need to leave the house.
\pop[3]Those are pretty confidential, so we can wait outside.
But for your shifts, I assume we can just hang out in the store?
\pop[3]Hiding in the store to avoid people.
Kinda reminds me of how we first met.
Every good story ends how it begins.
\pop[3]I definitely hope ours isn't about to end.
It's like a vacation on top of my hiatus.
\pop[2]I feel like this is a good time to let them know that I might be cleared soon.
\pop[2]My counselor told me that it could only be a couple more sessions away, too.
Hopefully he's been sticking to the curriculum, lately.
\pop[4]I'm really glad to hear that, Delta.
Getting cleared is a big deal.
\pop[4]Delta has to see a counselor. You know, someone to talk to.
People without visions can be more emotionally compromised.
\pop[3]And I guess this is a sign that they aren't?
I wouldn't mind trying some more of that beer, either.
\pop[3]Hah. It really grows on you, doesn't it?
Hated it at first, but now you can't get enough of it.
\pop[3]Yeah. Kinda how I feel about you.
Gotta give you credit for the sass, though.
I should add you to the group chat.
\pop[4]It might be best to use that a lot.
Especially if we're talking about "matters at hand".
Sometimes security and surveillance can be a two-way street.
You're scaring me, but it makes sense.
\pop[2]All the technology belonged to \c[23]Argus\c[0], after all.
\pop[2]I wonder if they could watch "people of note".
\pop[4]Just being cautious. I don't think they'd actually do something like that.
The user-agreement is pretty clear on their... ethical limitations.
\pop[3]Ready to get this show on the road?
\pop[2]I let them know that my next appointment is tomorrow.
\pop[2]It's in the morning though, pretty bright and early.
\pop[4]Good. Then we can head to my shift right after.
I start in the afternoon, and close up shop.
\pop[3]Oh, could we head back to that plane?
I left some stuff there by accident.
\pop[3]Isaac hooked me up with some cash, so yeah.
It's nothing major, but I'd hate to leave it all behind.
\pop[3]You're all still good if I stream?
I was supposed to go live in a little bit.
\pop[3]Go for it. We won't bother you.
In fact, I might watch along.
\pop[4]Yeah, today will probably be pretty boring.
Let's get Kyron into the chat, and waste some time.
